    "id": "i-have-atcs-but-zero-purchases-my-product-page-looks",
    "slug": "i-have-atcs-but-zero-purchases-my-product-page-looks",
    "question": "I have ATCs but zero purchases. My product page looks fine. What's actually wrong?",
    "answerHTML": "\n<div class=\"faq-origin-tag\">Appears in nearly every testing discussion — extremely common</div>\n<p>This is the ATC abandonment problem. When your ATC rate is good (above 5%) but your purchase rate is near zero, you have a <strong>checkout friction problem</strong>, not a traffic problem. Common causes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Unexpected shipping cost at checkout:</strong> If your product page says \"free shipping\" but Shopify charges $5.99 at checkout, expect 40–60% cart abandonment from that discrepancy alone.</li>\n<li><strong>Payment options missing:</strong> A significant percentage of buyers expect PayPal. If you only have Shopify Payments (card), you're losing everyone who doesn't feel safe entering card details on an unfamiliar store.</li>\n<li><strong>Trust collapse at checkout:</strong> No trust badges. No SSL visible. Unfamiliar brand name on the checkout URL. Buyers who were interested on the product page get cold feet at payment.</li>\n<li><strong>Checkout page load time:</strong> On mobile 3G, a 4+ second checkout load drops conversions measurably. Compress everything. Run Google PageSpeed Insights on your checkout URL.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Go to Shopify Analytics → Sessions → Checkout Started → Completed. Find the exact drop-off point. If 80% are abandoning at the payment page, it's trust. If they're abandoning at the shipping estimate, it's pricing friction.\n    <div class=\"inline-tools-label\">CRO &amp; Analytics Tools</div>\n<div class=\"inline-tools-grid\">\n<a class=\"itkc\" href=\"https://hotjar.com\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">\n<div class=\"itkc-logo\"><img alt=\"Hotjar\" onerror=\"this.parentNode.innerHTML='🔥'\" src=\"/images/hotjar.png\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"/></div>\n<div class=\"itkc-info\"><div class=\"itkc-name\">Hotjar</div><div class=\"itkc-desc\">Heatmaps + session recordings — see exactly where visitors drop</div></div>\n<span class=\"itkc-cta\">Try Free</span>\n</a>\n<a class=\"itkc\" href=\"https://intelligems.io\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">\n<div class=\"itkc-logo\"><img alt=\"Intelligems\" onerror=\"this.parentNode.innerHTML='🧪'\" src=\"/images/intelligems.jpeg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"/></div>\n<div class=\"itkc-info\"><div class=\"itkc-name\">Intelligems</div><div class=\"itkc-desc\">A/B test your pricing — find the optimal price point with data</div></div>\n<span class=\"itkc-cta\">Try Free</span>\n</a>\n</div></p>\n<div class=\"faq-tactical-box\"><strong>Tactical Fix</strong>Add all payment methods available in your market (PayPal is non-negotiable). Make shipping cost explicit on the product page before checkout. Add trust badges directly above the buy button. Run a test order yourself on your phone to see exactly what the experience feels like.</div>\n",
    "answerText": "This is the ATC abandonment problem. When your ATC rate is good (above 5%) but your purchase rate is near zero, you have a checkout friction problem, not a traffic problem. Common causes: Unexpected shipping cost at checkout: If your product page says \"free shipping\" but Shopify charges $5.99 at checkout, expect 40–60% cart abandonment from that discrepancy alone. Payment options missing: A significant percentage of buyers expect PayPal. If you only have Shopify Payments (card), you're losing everyone who doesn't feel safe entering card details on an unfamiliar store. Trust collapse at checkout: No trust badges. No SSL visible. Unfamiliar brand name on the checkout URL. Buyers who were interested on the product page get cold feet at payment. Checkout page load time: On mobile 3G, a 4+ second checkout load drops conversions measurably. Compress everything. Run Google PageSpeed Insights on your checkout URL. Go to Shopify Analytics → Sessions → Checkout Started → Completed. Find the exact drop-off point. If 80% are abandoning at the payment page, it's trust. If they're abandoning at the shipping estimate, it's pricing friction. CRO & Analytics Tools HotjarHeatmaps + session recordings — see exactly where visitors drop Try Free IntelligemsA/B test your pricing — find the optimal price point with data Try Free Tactical FixAdd all payment methods available in your market (PayPal is non-negotiable). Make shipping cost explicit on the product page before checkout. Add trust badges directly above the buy button. Run a test order yourself on your phone to see exactly what the experience feels like.",
    "category": "Meta Ads",
