    "id": "should-i-run-ads-on-weekends-my-performance-always-tanks",
    "slug": "should-i-run-ads-on-weekends-my-performance-always-tanks",
    "question": "Should I run ads on weekends? My performance always tanks on Saturdays.",
    "answerHTML": "\n<div class=\"faq-origin-tag\">Frequently observed pattern — operators often misattribute weekend drops to ad quality</div>\n<p>Weekend performance variation is real and structural, not a creative problem. Consumer behavior on social media differs significantly between weekdays and weekends in ways that affect your metrics.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>CPMs are often higher on weekends:</strong> More advertisers running weekend promotions = more competition for impressions = higher cost to reach the same audience.</li>\n<li><strong>Purchase intent shifts:</strong> People browsing social media on a Saturday afternoon are in a different mindset than a Tuesday evening browser. Problem-aware buying often happens on weekdays when people are dealing with work/life friction that reminds them of the problem your product solves.</li>\n<li><strong>What to actually do:</strong> Don't kill your campaigns on weekends — pausing and restarting disrupts learning phase. Instead, use weekday vs. weekend data to inform your budget scheduling. Some operators use automated rules to reduce budget 30–40% on Saturday-Sunday and increase it back on Monday.</li>\n<li><strong>Niche matters:</strong> Leisure, hobby, and home products often perform better on weekends. B2B-adjacent products often worse. Know your persona's weekly rhythm.</li>\n</ul>\n",
    "answerText": "Weekend performance variation is real and structural, not a creative problem. Consumer behavior on social media differs significantly between weekdays and weekends in ways that affect your metrics. CPMs are often higher on weekends: More advertisers running weekend promotions = more competition for impressions = higher cost to reach the same audience. Purchase intent shifts: People browsing social media on a Saturday afternoon are in a different mindset than a Tuesday evening browser. Problem-aware buying often happens on weekdays when people are dealing with work/life friction that reminds them of the problem your product solves. What to actually do: Don't kill your campaigns on weekends — pausing and restarting disrupts learning phase. Instead, use weekday vs. weekend data to inform your budget scheduling. Some operators use automated rules to reduce budget 30–40% on Saturday-Sunday and increase it back on Monday. Niche matters: Leisure, hobby, and home products often perform better on weekends. B2B-adjacent products often worse. Know your persona's weekly rhythm.",
    "category": "Meta Ads",
    "targetKeyword": "should i run ads on weekends my performance always tanks on saturdays.",
    "metaDescription": "Weekend performance variation is real and structural, not a creative problem. Consumer behavior on social media differs significantly between weekdays and…"
