    "slug": "do-i-need-a-us-llc-to-run-meta-ads",
    "question": "Do I need a US LLC to run Meta ads? I'm not based in the US.",
    "answerHTML": "\n<div class=\"faq-origin-tag\">Consistent confusion among non-US operators — delays launches by weeks</div>\n<p><strong>No. You do not need a US LLC to run Meta ads.</strong> You can run ads as an individual with a foreign card in many cases. This is a very common misconception that delays non-US operators by weeks while they sort out business formations they don't need yet.</p>\n<p>What you actually need: a valid payment method, a personal Facebook account in good standing, and a Business Manager. That's it to run ads. The LLC matters for different reasons:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Payment processor compliance:</strong> Stripe and PayPal US accounts require a US entity. If you want US-based processing, you'll eventually want a US LLC.</li>\n<div class=\"inline-tools-label\">When You Need an LLC</div>\n<div class=\"inline-tools-grid\">\n<a class=\"itkc\" href=\"https://bizee.com\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">\n<div class=\"itkc-logo\"><img alt=\"Bizee\" onerror=\"this.parentNode.innerHTML='⚡'\" src=\"/images/bizee.png\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"/></div>\n<div class=\"itkc-info\"><div class=\"itkc-name\">Bizee</div><div class=\"itkc-desc\">Free LLC formation — state fees only</div></div>\n<span class=\"itkc-cta\">Form Free</span>\n</a>\n<a class=\"itkc\" href=\"https://zenbusiness.com\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">\n<div class=\"itkc-logo\"><img alt=\"ZenBusiness\" onerror=\"this.parentNode.innerHTML='🏢'\" src=\"/images/zenbusiness.png\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"/></div>\n<div class=\"itkc-info\"><div class=\"itkc-name\">ZenBusiness</div><div class=\"itkc-desc\">LLC + registered agent from $0</div></div>\n<span class=\"itkc-cta\">Form LLC</span>\n</a>\n<a class=\"itkc\" href=\"https://filenow.com\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">\n<div class=\"itkc-logo\"><img alt=\"FileNow\" onerror=\"this.parentNode.innerHTML='📋'\" src=\"/images/filenow.jpeg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"/></div>\n<div class=\"itkc-info\"><div class=\"itkc-name\">FileNow</div><div class=\"itkc-desc\">Business filing + ongoing compliance support</div></div>\n<span class=\"itkc-cta\">Try Free</span>\n</a>\n</div>\n<li><strong>Bank accounts:</strong> US business bank accounts require a US entity. Wise, Mercury, and similar fintechs are alternatives.</li>\n<li><strong>Liability protection:</strong> An LLC protects personal assets. Once you're doing real revenue, this matters. At zero revenue, it's premature optimization.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Start running ads now. Sort out the entity structure once you're profitable and processing real volume.</p>\n",
    "answerText": "No. You do not need a US LLC to run Meta ads. You can run ads as an individual with a foreign card in many cases. This is a very common misconception that delays non-US operators by weeks while they sort out business formations they don't need yet. What you actually need: a valid payment method, a personal Facebook account in good standing, and a Business Manager. That's it to run ads. The LLC matters for different reasons: Payment processor compliance: Stripe and PayPal US accounts require a US entity. If you want US-based processing, you'll eventually want a US LLC. When You Need an LLC BizeeFree LLC formation — state fees only Form Free ZenBusinessLLC + registered agent from $0 Form LLC FileNowBusiness filing + ongoing compliance support Try Free Bank accounts: US business bank accounts require a US entity. Wise, Mercury, and similar fintechs are alternatives. Liability protection: An LLC protects personal assets. Once you're doing real revenue, this matters. At zero revenue, it's premature optimization. Start running ads now. Sort out the entity structure once you're profitable and processing real volume.",
