    "slug": "should-i-use-a-professional-domain-email-or-is-gmail",
    "question": "Should I use a professional domain email or is Gmail fine for my store?",
    "answerHTML": "\n<div class=\"faq-origin-tag\">Professional appearance question — consistently asked by beginners setting up their first store</div>\n<p><strong>Use a domain email from day one.</strong> A contact email of support@yourbrandname.com vs. yourbrandname2025@gmail.com is a measurable trust signal that affects store conversion rate — particularly on cold traffic that's evaluating whether your store is legitimate.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>How to set it up cheaply:</strong> Google Workspace is $6/month and gives you a professional email at your domain. Alternatively, Zoho Mail has a free tier. Route the professional email to your regular inbox if you prefer managing everything in one place.</li>\n<li><strong>Where to show it:</strong> In your store footer, on the checkout page, in email flows, and in your store's Shopify contact settings. Consistency across all touchpoints builds trust signals.</li>\n<li><strong>Spam risk of Gmail:</strong> Using a Gmail address for transactional emails (order confirmations, shipping updates) is also a deliverability red flag. ESPs like Klaviyo and your Shopify notifications should send from a domain email to maximize inbox delivery rates.</li>\n</ul>\n",
    "answerText": "Use a domain email from day one. A contact email of support@yourbrandname.com vs. yourbrandname2025@gmail.com is a measurable trust signal that affects store conversion rate — particularly on cold traffic that's evaluating whether your store is legitimate. How to set it up cheaply: Google Workspace is $6/month and gives you a professional email at your domain. Alternatively, Zoho Mail has a free tier. Route the professional email to your regular inbox if you prefer managing everything in one place. Where to show it: In your store footer, on the checkout page, in email flows, and in your store's Shopify contact settings. Consistency across all touchpoints builds trust signals. Spam risk of Gmail: Using a Gmail address for transactional emails (order confirmations, shipping updates) is also a deliverability red flag. ESPs like Klaviyo and your Shopify notifications should send from a domain email to maximize inbox delivery rates.",
