    "id": "my-frequency-is-going-above-3-should-i-be-worried",
    "slug": "my-frequency-is-going-above-3-should-i-be-worried",
    "question": "My frequency is going above 3. Should I be worried?",
    "answerHTML": "\n<p>Frequency above 3 means your audience has seen your ad an average of 3 times. Whether that's a problem depends entirely on your campaign scale and CPM trend. Signs it's becoming a problem: CPM is rising (audience fatigue), CTR is falling week over week, CPA is climbing despite stable spend. Signs it's fine: metrics are stable, you're running broad targeting, the campaign is still profitable. At small budgets ($50-200/day) high frequency is expected — you have a limited audience at that spend. It only becomes critical when you're spending $500+/day and frequency is above 5-6.</p>\n<div class=\"faq-tactical-box\"><strong>Tactical Fix</strong>If frequency is climbing AND performance is declining: add new creatives immediately, test new creative angles, or expand geo targeting. If frequency is climbing but performance is stable: don't panic, but have new creatives ready as a preemptive move.</div>\n",
    "answerText": "Frequency above 3 means your audience has seen your ad an average of 3 times. Whether that's a problem depends entirely on your campaign scale and CPM trend. Signs it's becoming a problem: CPM is rising (audience fatigue), CTR is falling week over week, CPA is climbing despite stable spend. Signs it's fine: metrics are stable, you're running broad targeting, the campaign is still profitable. At small budgets ($50-200/day) high frequency is expected — you have a limited audience at that spend. It only becomes critical when you're spending $500+/day and frequency is above 5-6. Tactical FixIf frequency is climbing AND performance is declining: add new creatives immediately, test new creative angles, or expand geo targeting. If frequency is climbing but performance is stable: don't panic, but have new creatives ready as a preemptive move.",
    "category": "Reading Ad Data",
    "targetKeyword": "my frequency is going above 3. should i be worried",
    "metaDescription": "Frequency above 3 means your audience has seen your ad an average of 3 times. Whether that's a problem depends entirely on your campaign scale and CPM…"
,
